76561198031021417,Not Recommended,244410,10168518,"Posted: 19 May, 2014",all,Kutterscholle,"Maybe its because I´m new to the Supreme-Ruler-series, but I cannot recommend this game. For long-time strategy players like me its just to arcade-like in its warfare part. But its easier to make a list anyway.PROs- the economic side is cool. You can built and reinforce your economic sectors in six categories and three manufactured goods. Plus you trade surplus and buy things you lack with ease.- the builtup for war is easy. Units are built with land-/naval-/aircraft-factories in different cities. Plus you can hold them in reserve so they don´t clutter the map and cost immense resources- I like the importance of recon units and the extra range of artillery. Makes the tactical combat fun.CONs- research is far reaching, but the easy way to trade it, destroys the fun. If you have researched the general tech, you can trade or buy unit-schemes from friends (or just anybody) for next to nothing. As Italy I ended up with advanced carriers of Japanese design and cool German recon units. Plus I think that there should be far more not tradeable research areas, so it´s more difficult to excel in research as a minor nation.- producing units is very cheap, so you end up piling up units in reserve. which leads to:- in my view your armies are far to vast to really control them properly in all theatres. So you end up losing small or prestigious units somewhere without even noticing it right away. Even units like carriers can be destroyed in seconds (which I did) or four submarine in a wolfpack are oblitarated in a glimpse. Its better in land and air combat, but naval combat just goes on to fast.- the AI is not useless, but not very clever either. For example: As Germany attacked Poland the Western front to France was unguarded. Later it tried an invasion of Britain only with (zillions) of transports risking a good portion of its army. Fortunatly for Germany the British navy drove around aimlessly.- the manual does not explain very much. So I looked in forums and learned much the ""hard way"" via losing.For me Supreme Ruler 1936 has many fun aspects, but it´s not properly balanced and too confusing in large scale combat. The AI is not clever enough to watch theatres for you (not mentioning your Allies) so you win mostly by sheer numbers."
