76561198043685721,Not Recommended,244410,10149748,"Posted: 17 May, 2014",all,Atreides,"Though this game can probably be very enjoyable, in it's current state I don't recommend it to new players to the Supreme Ruler series.Basic game mechanics are explained only superficially in a short tutorial. Understanding warfare, diplomacy, research and how to manage your economy and population will require you to wade through a wiki made for other games in the Supreme Ruler series, which isn't completely applicable to Supreme Ruler 1936. The Steam community luckily is helpful to a point, however a game company can't just leave the responsibility of getting to know the basics of a game to the community.IMHO a game company delivers an incomplete product, when it doesn't give you an adequate manual or at least a decent tutorial with the full release of a game. This holds especially true for a complex game like Supreme Ruler 1936. Instead you are left to mostly figure the game out for yourself."
